div.p:
Noting that no proposal concerning the breadth of
                            the territorial sea or fishing rights in a contiguous zone received the
                            two-thirds majority required for adoption by the Conference;

Considering, however, that both of these important
                            matters were extensively discussed at the Conference so that nations are
                            fully cognizant of each other’s problems with respect thereto;

list.item:
Requests the Secretary-General to convoke
                                the conference in August, 1959 or as soon thereafter as possible,
                                at________;
